    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In the v2.1 spec it seems like it is a new endpoint, but in reality it isn't. There was an EIP a long time ago, which specified the endpoint: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-695\r\n\r\nWe have this [already implemented](https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/Reference/API-Methods/#eth_chainid). \r\nIn the current implementation we return a hex value, which is correct because `uint` is indeed a hex value per spec: https://github.com/ethereum/execution-apis/blob/188589473adb07a48f11fcb0d687d159e790b8a4/src/schemas/base-types.json#L42\r\n",
